<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 12:08AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Baldwin, east central Putnam, western Hancock and southeastern Greene
Counties through 1245 AM EDT...
At 1207 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Devereux, or 10 miles
west of Sparta, moving north at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Milledgeville, Sparta, White Plains, Reynolds at Lake Oconee,
Liberty, Rockville, Devereux, Beulah, Underwood, Shoulderbone and
Oconee Springs Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
